column2: VARDESC
Marijuana makes small things seem intensely interesting.
Smoking marijuana makes me hungry.
Smoking marijuana increases my craving for things.
I get a sense of relaxation from smoking marijuana.
Smoking marijuana makes me less tense or relieves anxiety; it helps me to unwind.
Marijuana makes me carefree, and I do not care about my problems as much.
I am not concerned about how others evaluate me when I am on marijuana.
Marijuana makes me talk more than usual.
I feel like I can focus on one thing better when I smoke marijuana.
When I smoke marijuana I do not feel insecure.
Marijuana makes me say things I do not mean.
I am more sociable when I smoke marijuana.
Smoking marijuana makes me feel like part of the group.
If I have been smoking marijuana, it is harder for me to concentrate and understand the meaning of what is being said.
Marijuana slows thinking and actions.
I become more creative or imaginative on marijuana.
If I have been smoking marijuana it is harder to remember things.
Things seem unreal and I feel out of touch with what is going on around me when I smoke marijuana.
When I smoke marijuana it helps me escape reality.
Marijuana makes me giggly and laugh a lot.
When I smoke marijuana I feel like I have heavy feet and no coordination.
Music sounds different when I smoke marijuana.
Marijuana tastes and smells bad.
I have a happy, good feeling when I smoke marijuana.
Marijuana causes me to lose control and become careless.
Marijuana makes it easier to escape from problems and responsibilities.
I am less motivated when I smoke marijuana.
Marijuana can cause me to become depressed and disappointed with myself.
Marijuana causes euphoria (strong sense of well-being).
Marijuana can make my feelings change from happy to sad.
I act excited when I smoke marijuana.
Marijuana does not make me feel more romantic or attracted to members of the opposite sex.
After smoking marijuana my eyelids feel heavy and I become drowsy.
Marijuana can make me angry and possibly violent.
After the "high" of smoking marijuana, I feel down.
Marijuana does not alter my personality.
I feel sexy or more interested in sex after smoking marijuana.
Marijuana makes me critical and short-tempered.
I get the "munchies" (craving for snacks) when I smoke marijuana.
It is difficult for me to express my thoughts clearly if I have been smoking marijuana.
Marijuana makes my mouth seem dry.
Marijuana makes me calm.
Marijuana changes my perception of time and distance.
I am more relaxed in social situations if I have been smoking marijuana.
I have a better time at parties if I am smoking marijuana.
Marijuana makes reaction times slower.
I am more willing to do things that I normally would not do when I smoke marijuana.
Smoking marijuana is similar to being “high” from drinking alcohol.
